Dec 28-1930 
Grinnell Iow.
My Dear little girl-
As Ever your presence was very dear and near when I opened the package containing the box of lovely handkerchief making quite an addition the lovely ones of other Christmas so dainty - so dainty! so sweet, so thotful just like your own dear little self.-Santa Clause was very kind this year my 72nd birthday & christmas - I came here the 16 of Nov. just to get away from pointer housekeeping and Expect to stay until the first of march or until the weather is nice down in the Ozarks. John and Mona have moved back to their home in Branson and they will <unclear/> after my home, - Sister and I am making rugs and piecing quilts I expect to go to Lulu's sometime before I return to Branson. 

27
girl I wish you could come to us again, It has been a long time since you were there. John has two cars now Enid and HIlda both drive and of course Sigurd when he is home He came home from St Louis to spend xmas - He is going to the Rankin mechan-ical School - will finish this year, can you realize that Enid and Sigurd are grown - Enid 19 and a very, Efficient Stenographer - Is at home doing the <unclear/> rotary work for her father John says she is fine, and she is so pretty not one bed of the flupper about her - Sigurd is a fine looking boy and doing fine in School, Hilda you remember her as a dear little girl. She is not large for her agents in the Second year of High school and leading all her classe 14 in Dec Alice the apple of Grandma's eye in the foruth grade and a star pupil, loved by Every one - Hilda has the kind of brother father has, is her father's <unclear/> to. 

